      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>In the <i>Gatterman–Koch reaction,</i> a formyl group ( – CHO) is introduced directly onto a benzene ring. For example, reaction of toluene with CO and HCl in the presence of mixed CuCl/AlCl<sub>3</sub> gives <i>p</i>-methylbenzaldehyde. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbXNWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1fd2186ec584f94e24be84a89b804d6d5a4f72b1/OChem_16_EC_029.jpg\" alt=\"Toluene reacts with carbon monoxide and hydrogen chloride in the presence of copper (1) chloride or aluminum trichloride to form toluene with an aldehyde group in the para position.\">",
